{
  "local_port": 52150,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best places to eat vegetarian food in New Delhi?",
  "response": "New Delhi is a paradise for vegetarians, offering a wide array of culinary delights that cater to diverse tastes. Here are some of the best places to enjoy vegetarian food in the city:\n\n---\n\n### **Fine Dining & Upscale Restaurants**\n1. **Indian Accent** (The Lodhi)  \n   - Offers innovative Indian vegetarian dishes with a modern twist.  \n   - Must-try: Vegetarian tasting menu.\n\n2. **Safdarjung's** (Taj Ambassador)  \n   - Known for its elegant North Indian vegetarian cuisine.  \n   - Must-try: Dal Safdarjung and paneer dishes.\n\n3. **Amaranta** (The Oberoi)  \n   - Focuses on coastal Indian vegetarian cuisine with a refined touch.  \n   - Must-try: Avocado chaat and jackfruit biryani.\n\n---\n\n### **Casual Dining & Cafes**\n4. **Saravana Bhavan** (Connaught Place)  \n   - A popular South Indian vegetarian restaurant known for its dosas and thalis.  \n   - Must-try: Masala dosa and filter coffee.\n\n5. **Sattvik** (Saket)  \n   - Offers pure vegetarian food with a focus on organic and healthy ingredients.  \n   - Must-try: Sattvik thali and millet-based dishes.\n\n6. **Carnatic Cafe** (Hauz Khas)  \n   - Specializes in South Indian vegetarian street food and snacks.  \n   - Must-try: Paniyaram and vada pav.\n\n---\n\n### **Street Food & Local Favorites**\n7. **Natraj Dahi Bhalle Wala** (Chandni Chowk)  \n   - Famous for its dahi bhalle and chaat.  \n   - A must-visit for authentic Delhi street food.\n\n8. **Kake Di Hatti** (Chandni Chowk)  \n   - Known for its massive and delicious vegetarian stuffed parathas.  \n   - Must-try: Aloo paratha with dollops of butter.\n\n9. **Bengali Sweet House** (Defence Colony)  \n   - Offers a variety of vegetarian snacks and sweets.  \n   - Must-try: Paneer tikka and kachori.\n\n---\n\n### **Healthy & Organic Options**\n10. **Fabcafe by Fabindia** (Multiple locations)  \n   - Focuses on organic and wholesome vegetarian meals.  \n   - Must-try: Quinoa biryani and detox salads.\n\n11. **Greenr Caf\u00e9** (Cyber Hub, Gurgaon)  \n   - A trendy caf\u00e9 offering vegetarian and vegan options.  \n   - Must-try: Buddha bowls and vegan desserts.\n\n---\n\n### **Ethnic & Regional Cuisine**\n12. **Rajdhani Thali Restaurant** (Connaught Place)  \n   - Offers a traditional Rajasthani/Gujarati thali experience.  \n   - Must-try: Unlimited thali with dal, kadhi, and assorted sweets.\n\n13. **Udupi Veg** (Green Park)  \n   - A classic Udupi vegetarian restaurant known for its South Indian fare.  \n   - Must-try: Rava dosa and Mysore pak.\n\n14. **Karnataka Food Center** (Majnu Ka Tila)  \n   - A hidden gem for authentic South Indian vegetarian dishes.  \n   - Must-try: Akki roti and bisibelebath.\n\n---\n\n### **International Vegetarian Options**\n15. **Veganarie Caf\u00e9** (Saket)  \n   - A vegan-friendly caf\u00e9 offering international dishes.  \n   - Must-try: Vegan pizzas and dairy-free desserts.\n\n16. **Rose Caf\u00e9** (Hauz Khas)  \n   - A charming caf\u00e9 with vegetarian and vegan options.  \n   - Must-try: Veggie sandwiches and smoothies.\n\n---\n\n### **Sweet Treats**\n17. **Giani\u2019s** (Chandni Chowk)  \n   - Famous for its rabri falooda and kulfi.  \n   - A must-visit for dessert lovers.\n\n18. **Bikanervala** (Multiple locations)  \n   - Offers a variety of vegetarian snacks and sweets.  \n   - Must-try: Rasgulla and samosas.\n\n---\n\nWhether you're craving traditional Indian fare, street food, or international vegetarian dishes, New Delhi has something to satisfy every palate. Enjoy your culinary journey! \ud83c\udf31\u2728",
  "temperature": 1.0,
